3440
3441static isc_result_t
3442dns_message_pseudosectiontoyaml(dns_message_t *msg,
3443 dns_pseudosection_t section,
3444 const dns_master_style_t *style,
3445 dns_messagetextflag_t flags,
3446 isc_buffer_t *target)
3447{
3448 dns_rdataset_t *ps = NULL;
3449 const dns_name_t *name = NULL;
3450 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3451 char buf[sizeof("1234567890")];
3452 uint32_t mbz;
3453 dns_rdata_t rdata;
3454 isc_buffer_t optbuf;
3455 uint16_t optcode, optlen;
3456 unsigned char *optdata;
3457 unsigned int saveindent = dns_master_indent;
3458
3459 REQUIRE(DNS_MESSAGE_VALID(msg));
3460 REQUIRE(target != NULL);
3461 REQUIRE(VALID_PSEUDOSECTION(section));
3462
3463 switch (section) {
3464 case DNS_PSEUDOSECTION_OPT:
3465 ps = dns_message_getopt(msg);
3466 if (ps == NULL) {
3467 goto cleanup;
3468 }
3469
3470 INDENT(style);
3471 ADD_STRING(target, "OPT_PSEUDOSECTION:\n");
3472 dns_master_indent++;
3473
3474 INDENT(style);
3475 ADD_STRING(target, "EDNS:\n");
3476 dns_master_indent++;
3477
3478 INDENT(style);
3479 ADD_STRING(target, "version: ");
3480 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%u",
3481 (unsigned int)((ps->ttl & 0x00ff0000) >> 16));
3482 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3483 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3484 INDENT(style);
3485 ADD_STRING(target, "flags:");
3486 if ((ps->ttl & DNS_MESSAGEEXTFLAG_DO) != 0)
3487 ADD_STRING(target, " do");
3488 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3489 mbz = ps->ttl & 0xffff;
3490 mbz &= ~DNS_MESSAGEEXTFLAG_DO; /* Known Flags. */
3491 if (mbz != 0) {
3492 INDENT(style);
3493 ADD_STRING(target, "MBZ: ");
3494 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "0x%.4x", mbz);
3495 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3496 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3497 }
3498 INDENT(style);
3499 ADD_STRING(target, "udp: ");
3500 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%u\n", (unsigned int)ps->rdclass);
3501 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3502 result = dns_rdataset_first(ps);
3503 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3504 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3505 goto cleanup;
3506 }
3507
3508 /*
3509 * Print EDNS info, if any.
3510 *
3511 * WARNING: The option contents may be malformed as
3512 * dig +ednsopt=value:<content> does not validity
3513 * checking.
3514 */
3515 dns_rdata_init(&rdata);
3516 dns_rdataset_current(ps, &rdata);
3517
3518 isc_buffer_init(&optbuf, rdata.data, rdata.length);
3519 isc_buffer_add(&optbuf, rdata.length);
3520 while (isc_buffer_remaininglength(&optbuf) != 0) {
3521 INSIST(isc_buffer_remaininglength(&optbuf) >= 4U);
3522 optcode = isc_buffer_getuint16(&optbuf);
3523 optlen = isc_buffer_getuint16(&optbuf);
3524 INSIST(isc_buffer_remaininglength(&optbuf) >= optlen);
3525
3526 if (optcode == DNS_OPT_NSID) {
3527 INDENT(style);
3528 ADD_STRING(target, "NSID");
3529 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_COOKIE) {
3530 INDENT(style);
3531 ADD_STRING(target, "COOKIE");
3532 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_CLIENT_SUBNET) {
3533 isc_buffer_t ecsbuf;
3534 INDENT(style);
3535 ADD_STRING(target, "CLIENT-SUBNET");
3536 isc_buffer_init(&ecsbuf,
3537 isc_buffer_current(&optbuf),
3538 optlen);
3539 isc_buffer_add(&ecsbuf, optlen);
3540 result = render_ecs(&ecsbuf, target);
3541 if (result == ISC_R_NOSPACE)
3542 goto cleanup;
3543 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3544 isc_buffer_forward(&optbuf, optlen);
3545 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3546 continue;
3547 }
3548 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3549 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_EXPIRE) {
3550 if (optlen == 4) {
3551 uint32_t secs;
3552 secs = isc_buffer_getuint32(&optbuf);
3553 INDENT(style);
3554 ADD_STRING(target, "EXPIRE: ");
3555 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%u", secs);
3556 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3557 ADD_STRING(target, " (");
3558 result = dns_ttl_totext(secs,
3559 true,
3560 true,
3561 target);
3562 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3563 goto cleanup;
3564 ADD_STRING(target, ")\n");
3565 continue;
3566 }
3567 INDENT(style);
3568 ADD_STRING(target, "EXPIRE");
3569 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_PAD) {
3570 INDENT(style);
3571 ADD_STRING(target, "PAD");
3572 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_KEY_TAG) {
3573 INDENT(style);
3574 ADD_STRING(target, "KEY-TAG");
3575 if (optlen > 0U && (optlen % 2U) == 0U) {
3576 const char *sep = ": ";
3577 uint16_t id;
3578 while (optlen > 0U) {
3579 id = isc_buffer_getuint16(&optbuf);
3580 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s%u",
3581 sep, id);
3582 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3583 sep = ", ";
3584 optlen -= 2;
3585 }
3586 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3587 continue;
3588 }
3589 } else {
3590 INDENT(style);
3591 ADD_STRING(target, "OPT: ");
3592 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%u", optcode);
3593 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3594 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3595 }
3596
3597 if (optlen != 0) {
3598 int i;
3599 ADD_STRING(target, ": ");
3600
3601 optdata = isc_buffer_current(&optbuf);
3602 for (i = 0; i < optlen; i++) {
3603 const char *sep;
3604 switch (optcode) {
3605 case DNS_OPT_COOKIE:
3606 sep = "";
3607 break;
3608 default:
3609 sep = " ";
3610 break;
3611 }
3612 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%02x%s",
3613 optdata[i], sep);
3614 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3615 }
3616
3617 isc_buffer_forward(&optbuf, optlen);
3618
3619 if (optcode == DNS_OPT_COOKIE) {
3620 /*
3621 * Valid server cookie?
3622 */
3623 if (msg->cc_ok && optlen >= 16)
3624 ADD_STRING(target, " (good)");
3625 /*
3626 * Server cookie is not valid but
3627 * we had our cookie echoed back.
3628 */
3629 if (msg->cc_ok && optlen < 16)
3630 ADD_STRING(target, " (echoed)");
3631 /*
3632 * We didn't get our cookie echoed
3633 * back.
3634 */
3635 if (msg->cc_bad)
3636 ADD_STRING(target, " (bad)");
3637 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3638 continue;
3639 }
3640
3641 if (optcode == DNS_OPT_CLIENT_SUBNET) {
3642 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3643 continue;
3644 }
3645
3646 /*
3647 * For non-COOKIE options, add a printable
3648 * version
3649 */
3650 ADD_STRING(target, "(\"");
3651 if (isc_buffer_availablelength(target) < optlen)
3652 {
3653 result = ISC_R_NOSPACE;
3654 goto cleanup;
3655 }
3656 for (i = 0; i < optlen; i++) {
3657 if (isprint(optdata[i]))
3658 isc_buffer_putmem(target,
3659 &optdata[i],
3660 1);
3661 else
3662 isc_buffer_putstr(target, ".");
3663 }
3664 ADD_STRING(target, "\")");
3665 }
3666 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3667 }
3668 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3669 goto cleanup;
3670 case DNS_PSEUDOSECTION_TSIG:
3671 ps = dns_message_gettsig(msg, &name);
3672 if (ps == NULL) {
3673 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3674 goto cleanup;
3675 }
3676 INDENT(style);
3677 ADD_STRING(target, "TSIG_PSEUDOSECTION:\n");
3678 result = dns_master_rdatasettotext(name, ps, style, target);
3679 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3680 goto cleanup;
3681 case DNS_PSEUDOSECTION_SIG0:
3682 ps = dns_message_getsig0(msg, &name);
3683 if (ps == NULL) {
3684 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3685 goto cleanup;
3686 }
3687 INDENT(style);
3688 ADD_STRING(target, "SIG0_PSEUDOSECTION:\n");
3689 result = dns_master_rdatasettotext(name, ps, style, target);
3690 if ((flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOHEADERS) == 0 &&
3691 (flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOCOMMENTS) == 0)
3692 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3693 goto cleanup;
3694 }
3695
3696 result = ISC_R_UNEXPECTED;
3697
3698 cleanup:
3699 dns_master_indent = saveindent;
3700 return (result);
3701}

3744 ADD_STRING(target, " do");
3745 mbz = ps->ttl & 0xffff;
3746 mbz &= ~DNS_MESSAGEEXTFLAG_DO; /* Known Flags. */
3747 if (mbz != 0) {
3748 ADD_STRING(target, "; MBZ: ");
3749 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "0x%.4x", mbz);
3750 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3751 ADD_STRING(target, ", udp: ");
3752 } else
3753 ADD_STRING(target, "; udp: ");
3754 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%u\n", (unsigned int)ps->rdclass);
3755 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3756
3757 result = dns_rdataset_first(ps);
3758 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)

3761 /*
3762 * Print EDNS info, if any.
3763 *
3764 * WARNING: The option contents may be malformed as
3765 * dig +ednsopt=value:<content> does no validity
3766 * checking.
3767 */
3768 dns_rdata_init(&rdata);
3769 dns_rdataset_current(ps, &rdata);
3770
3771 isc_buffer_init(&optbuf, rdata.data, rdata.length);
3772 isc_buffer_add(&optbuf, rdata.length);
3773 while (isc_buffer_remaininglength(&optbuf) != 0) {
3774 INSIST(isc_buffer_remaininglength(&optbuf) >= 4U);
3775 optcode = isc_buffer_getuint16(&optbuf);
3776 optlen = isc_buffer_getuint16(&optbuf);
3777

3779
3780 INDENT(style);
3781
3782 if (optcode == DNS_OPT_NSID) {
3783 ADD_STRING(target, "; NSID");
3784 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_COOKIE) {
3785 ADD_STRING(target, "; COOKIE");
3786 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_CLIENT_SUBNET) {
3787 isc_buffer_t ecsbuf;
3788
3789 ADD_STRING(target, "; CLIENT-SUBNET");

3791 isc_buffer_current(&optbuf),
3792 optlen);
3793 isc_buffer_add(&ecsbuf, optlen);
3794 result = render_ecs(&ecsbuf, target);
3795 if (result == ISC_R_NOSPACE)
3796 return (result);
3797 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3798 isc_buffer_forward(&optbuf, optlen);
3799 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3800 continue;
3801 }
3802 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_EXPIRE) {
3803 if (optlen == 4) {
3804 uint32_t secs;
3805 secs = isc_buffer_getuint32(&optbuf);

3808 ADD_STRING(target, buf);

3811 true,
3812 true,
3813 target);

3817 continue;

3821 if (optlen == 2) {

3823 dsecs = isc_buffer_getuint16(&optbuf);
3824 ADD_STRING(target, "; TCP KEEPALIVE:");
3825 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), " %u.%u",
3826 dsecs / 10U, dsecs % 10U);
3827 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3828 ADD_STRING(target, " secs\n");
3829 continue;
3830 }
3831 ADD_STRING(target, "; TCP KEEPALIVE");
3832 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_PAD) {
3833 ADD_STRING(target, "; PAD");
3834 if (optlen > 0U) {
3835 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf),
3836 " (%u bytes)", optlen);
3837 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3838 isc_buffer_forward(&optbuf, optlen);
3839 }
3840 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3841 continue;
3842 } else if (optcode == DNS_OPT_KEY_TAG) {
3843 ADD_STRING(target, "; KEY-TAG");
3844 if (optlen > 0U && (optlen % 2U) == 0U) {
3845 const char *sep = ": ";
3846 uint16_t id;
3847 while (optlen > 0U) {
3848 id = isc_buffer_getuint16(&optbuf);
3849 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s%u",
3850 sep, id);
3851 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3852 sep = ", ";
3853 optlen -= 2;
3854 }
3855 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3856 continue;
3857 }
3858 } else {
3859 ADD_STRING(target, "; OPT=");
3860 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%u", optcode);
3861 ADD_STRING(target, buf);

3865 int i;
3866 ADD_STRING(target, ": ");

3868 optdata = isc_buffer_current(&optbuf);
3869 for (i = 0; i < optlen; i++) {
3870 const char *sep;
3871 switch (optcode) {
3872 case DNS_OPT_COOKIE:
3873 sep = "";
3874 break;
3875 default:
3876 sep = " ";
3877 break;
3878 }
3879 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%02x%s",
3880 optdata[i], sep);
3881 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3882 }
3883
3884 isc_buffer_forward(&optbuf, optlen);
3885
3886 if (optcode == DNS_OPT_COOKIE) {
3887 /*
3888 * Valid server cookie?
3889 */
3890 if (msg->cc_ok && optlen >= 16)
3891 ADD_STRING(target, " (good)");
3892 /*
3893 * Server cookie is not valid but
3894 * we had our cookie echoed back.
3895 */
3896 if (msg->cc_ok && optlen < 16)
3897 ADD_STRING(target, " (echoed)");
3898 /*
3899 * We didn't get our cookie echoed
3900 * back.
3901 */
3902 if (msg->cc_bad)
3903 ADD_STRING(target, " (bad)");
3904 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3905 continue;
3906 }
3907
3908 if (optcode == DNS_OPT_CLIENT_SUBNET) {
3909 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3910 continue;
3911 }
3912
3913 /*
3914 * For non-COOKIE options, add a printable
3915 * version
3916 */
3917 ADD_STRING(target, "(\"");
3918 if (isc_buffer_availablelength(target) < optlen)
3919 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
3920 for (i = 0; i < optlen; i++) {
3921 if (isprint(optdata[i]))
3922 isc_buffer_putmem(target,
3923 &optdata[i],
3924 1);
3925 else
3926 isc_buffer_putstr(target, ".");
3927 }
3928 ADD_STRING(target, "\")");
3929 }
3930 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3931 }
3932 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3933 case DNS_PSEUDOSECTION_TSIG:
3934 ps = dns_message_gettsig(msg, &name);
3935 if (ps == NULL)
3936 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3937 INDENT(style);
3938 if ((flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOCOMMENTS) == 0)
3939 ADD_STRING(target, ";; TSIG PSEUDOSECTION:\n");
3940 result = dns_master_rdatasettotext(name, ps, style, target);
3941 if ((flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOHEADERS) == 0 &&
3942 (flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOCOMMENTS) == 0)
3943 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3944 return (result);
3945 case DNS_PSEUDOSECTION_SIG0:
3946 ps = dns_message_getsig0(msg, &name);
3947 if (ps == NULL)
3948 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3949 INDENT(style);
3950 if ((flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOCOMMENTS) == 0)
3951 ADD_STRING(target, ";; SIG0 PSEUDOSECTION:\n");
3952 result = dns_master_rdatasettotext(name, ps, style, target);
3953 if ((flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOHEADERS) == 0 &&
3954 (flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOCOMMENTS) == 0)
3955 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3956 return (result);
3957 }
3958 result = ISC_R_UNEXPECTED;
3959 cleanup:
3960 return (result);
3961}

3963isc_result_t
3964dns_message_totext(dns_message_t *msg, const dns_master_style_t *style,
3965 dns_messagetextflag_t flags, isc_buffer_t *target)
3966{
3967 char buf[sizeof("1234567890")];
3968 isc_result_t result;
3969
3970 REQUIRE(DNS_MESSAGE_VALID(msg));
3971 REQUIRE(target != NULL);
3972
3973 if (((flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOHEADERS) == 0) &&
3974 (dns_master_styleflags(style) & DNS_STYLEFLAG_YAML))
3975 {
3976 INDENT(style);
3977 ADD_STRING(target, "opcode: ");
3978 ADD_STRING(target, opcodetext[msg->opcode]);
3979 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3980 INDENT(style);
3981 ADD_STRING(target, "status: ");
3982 result = dns_rcode_totext(msg->rcode, target);
3983 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3984 return (result);
3985 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3986 INDENT(style);
3987 ADD_STRING(target, "id: ");
3988 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%6u", msg->id);
3989 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
3990 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
3991 INDENT(style);
3992 ADD_STRING(target, "flags:");
3993 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_QR) != 0)
3994 ADD_STRING(target, " qr");
3995 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_AA) != 0)
3996 ADD_STRING(target, " aa");
3997 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_TC) != 0)
3998 ADD_STRING(target, " tc");
3999 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_RD) != 0)
4000 ADD_STRING(target, " rd");
4001 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_RA) != 0)
4002 ADD_STRING(target, " ra");
4003 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_AD) != 0)
4004 ADD_STRING(target, " ad");
4005 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_CD) != 0)
4006 ADD_STRING(target, " cd");
4007 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
4008 /*
4009 * The final unnamed flag must be zero.
4010 */
4011 if ((msg->flags & 0x0040U) != 0) {
4012 INDENT(style);
4013 ADD_STRING(target, "MBZ: 0x4");
4014 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
4015 }
4016 if (msg->opcode != dns_opcode_update) {
4017 INDENT(style);
4018 ADD_STRING(target, "QUESTION: ");
4019 } else {
4020 ADD_STRING(target, "ZONE: ");
4021 }
4022 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%1u",
4023 msg->counts[DNS_SECTION_QUESTION]);
4024 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
4025 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
4026 if (msg->opcode != dns_opcode_update) {
4027 INDENT(style);
4028 ADD_STRING(target, "ANSWER: ");
4029 } else {
4030 INDENT(style);
4031 ADD_STRING(target, "PREREQ: ");
4032 }
4033 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%1u",
4034 msg->counts[DNS_SECTION_ANSWER]);
4035 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
4036 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
4037 if (msg->opcode != dns_opcode_update) {
4038 INDENT(style);
4039 ADD_STRING(target, "AUTHORITY: ");
4040 } else {
4041 INDENT(style);
4042 ADD_STRING(target, "UPDATE: ");
4043 }
4044 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%1u",
4045 msg->counts[DNS_SECTION_AUTHORITY]);
4046 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
4047 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
4048 INDENT(style);
4049 ADD_STRING(target, "ADDITIONAL: ");
4050 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%1u",
4051 msg->counts[DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL]);
4052 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
4053 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
4054 } else if ((flags & DNS_MESSAGETEXTFLAG_NOHEADERS) == 0) {
4055 INDENT(style);
4056 ADD_STRING(target, ";; ->>HEADER<<- opcode: ");
4057 ADD_STRING(target, opcodetext[msg->opcode]);
4058 ADD_STRING(target, ", status: ");
4059 result = dns_rcode_totext(msg->rcode, target);
4060 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4061 return (result);
4062 ADD_STRING(target, ", id: ");
4063 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%6u", msg->id);
4064 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
4065 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
4066 INDENT(style);
4067 ADD_STRING(target, ";; flags:");
4068 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_QR) != 0)
4069 ADD_STRING(target, " qr");
4070 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_AA) != 0)
4071 ADD_STRING(target, " aa");
4072 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_TC) != 0)
4073 ADD_STRING(target, " tc");
4074 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_RD) != 0)
4075 ADD_STRING(target, " rd");
4076 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_RA) != 0)
4077 ADD_STRING(target, " ra");
4078 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_AD) != 0)
4079 ADD_STRING(target, " ad");
4080 if ((msg->flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_CD) != 0)
4081 ADD_STRING(target, " cd");
4082 /*
4083 * The final unnamed flag must be zero.
4084 */
4085 if ((msg->flags & 0x0040U) != 0) {
4086 INDENT(style);
4087 ADD_STRING(target, "; MBZ: 0x4");
4088 }
4089 if (msg->opcode != dns_opcode_update) {
4090 INDENT(style);
4091 ADD_STRING(target, "; QUESTION: ");
4092 } else {
4093 INDENT(style);
4094 ADD_STRING(target, "; ZONE: ");
4095 }
4096 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%1u",
4097 msg->counts[DNS_SECTION_QUESTION]);
4098 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
4099 if (msg->opcode != dns_opcode_update) {
4100 ADD_STRING(target, ", ANSWER: ");
4101 } else {
4102 ADD_STRING(target, ", PREREQ: ");
4103 }
4104 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%1u",
4105 msg->counts[DNS_SECTION_ANSWER]);
4106 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
4107 if (msg->opcode != dns_opcode_update) {
4108 ADD_STRING(target, ", AUTHORITY: ");
4109 } else {
4110 ADD_STRING(target, ", UPDATE: ");
4111 }
4112 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%1u",
4113 msg->counts[DNS_SECTION_AUTHORITY]);
4114 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
4115 ADD_STRING(target, ", ADDITIONAL: ");
4116 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%1u",
4117 msg->counts[DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL]);
4118 ADD_STRING(target, buf);
4119 ADD_STRING(target, "\n");
4120 }
4121 result = dns_message_pseudosectiontotext(msg,
4122 DNS_PSEUDOSECTION_OPT,
4123 style, flags, target);
4124 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4125 return (result);
4126
4127 result = dns_message_sectiontotext(msg, DNS_SECTION_QUESTION,
4128 style, flags, target);
4129 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4130 return (result);
4131 result = dns_message_sectiontotext(msg, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER,
4132 style, flags, target);
4133 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4134 return (result);
4135 result = dns_message_sectiontotext(msg, DNS_SECTION_AUTHORITY,
4136 style, flags, target);
4137 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4138 return (result);
4139 result = dns_message_sectiontotext(msg, DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL,
4140 style, flags, target);
4141 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4142 return (result);
4143
4144 result = dns_message_pseudosectiontotext(msg,
4145 DNS_PSEUDOSECTION_TSIG,
4146 style, flags, target);
4147 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4148 return (result);
4149
4150 result = dns_message_pseudosectiontotext(msg,
4151 DNS_PSEUDOSECTION_SIG0,
4152 style, flags, target);
4153 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4154 return (result);
4155
4156 cleanup:
4157 return (result);
4158}

4229
4230static void
4231logfmtpacket(dns_message_t *message, const char *description,
4232 const isc_sockaddr_t *address, isc_logcategory_t *category,
4233 isc_logmodule_t *module, const dns_master_style_t *style,
4234 int level, isc_mem_t *mctx)
4235{
4236 char addrbuf[ISC_SOCKADDR_FORMATSIZE] = { 0 };
4237 const char *newline = "\n";
4238 const char *space = " ";
4239 isc_buffer_t buffer;
4240 char *buf = NULL;
4241 int len = 1024;
4242 isc_result_t result;
4243
4244 if (! isc_log_wouldlog(dns_lctx, level))
4245 return;
4246
4247 /*
4248 * Note that these are multiline debug messages. We want a newline
4249 * to appear in the log after each message.
4250 */
4251
4252 if (address != NULL)
4253 isc_sockaddr_format(address, addrbuf, sizeof(addrbuf));
4254 else
4255 newline = space = "";
4256
4257 do {
4258 buf = isc_mem_get(mctx, len);
4259 if (buf == NULL)
4260 break;
4261 isc_buffer_init(&buffer, buf, len);
4262 result = dns_message_totext(message, style, 0, &buffer);
4263 if (result == ISC_R_NOSPACE) {
4264 isc_mem_put(mctx, buf, len);
4265 len += 1024;
4266 } else if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4267 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, category, module, level,
4268 "%s%s%s%s%.*s", description, space,
4269 addrbuf, newline,
4270 (int)isc_buffer_usedlength(&buffer),
4271 buf);
4272 } while (result == ISC_R_NOSPACE);
4273
4274 if (buf != NULL)
4275 isc_mem_put(mctx, buf, len);
4276}

4278isc_result_t
4279dns_message_buildopt(dns_message_t *message, dns_rdataset_t **rdatasetp,
4280 unsigned int version, uint16_t udpsize,
4281 unsigned int flags, dns_ednsopt_t *ednsopts, size_t count)
4282{
4283 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset = NULL;
4284 dns_rdatalist_t *rdatalist = NULL;
4285 dns_rdata_t *rdata = NULL;
4286 isc_result_t result;
4287 unsigned int len = 0, i;
4288
4289 REQUIRE(DNS_MESSAGE_VALID(message));
4290 REQUIRE(rdatasetp != NULL && *rdatasetp == NULL);
4291
4292 result = dns_message_gettemprdatalist(message, &rdatalist);
4293 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4294 return (result);
4295 result = dns_message_gettemprdata(message, &rdata);
4296 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4297 goto cleanup;
4298 result = dns_message_gettemprdataset(message, &rdataset);
4299 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4300 goto cleanup;
4301
4302 rdatalist->type = dns_rdatatype_opt;
4303
4304 /*
4305 * Set Maximum UDP buffer size.
4306 */
4307 rdatalist->rdclass = udpsize;
4308
4309 /*
4310 * Set EXTENDED-RCODE and Z to 0.
4311 */
4312 rdatalist->ttl = (version << 16);
4313 rdatalist->ttl |= (flags & 0xffff);
4314
4315 /*
4316 * Set EDNS options if applicable
4317 */
4318 if (count != 0U) {
4319 isc_buffer_t *buf = NULL;
4320 bool seenpad = false;
4321 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
4322 len += ednsopts[i].length + 4;
4323
4324 if (len > 0xffffU) {
4325 result = ISC_R_NOSPACE;
4326 goto cleanup;
4327 }
4328
4329 result = isc_buffer_allocate(message->mctx, &buf, len);
4330 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4331 goto cleanup;
4332
4333 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
4334 if (ednsopts[i].code == DNS_OPT_PAD &&
4335 ednsopts[i].length == 0U && !seenpad)
4336 {
4337 seenpad = true;
4338 continue;
4339 }
4340 isc_buffer_putuint16(buf, ednsopts[i].code);
4341 isc_buffer_putuint16(buf, ednsopts[i].length);
4342 if (ednsopts[i].length != 0) {
4343 isc_buffer_putmem(buf, ednsopts[i].value,
4344 ednsopts[i].length);
4345 }
4346 }
4347
4348 /* Padding must be the final option */
4349 if (seenpad) {
4350 isc_buffer_putuint16(buf, DNS_OPT_PAD);
4351 isc_buffer_putuint16(buf, 0);
4352 }
4353 rdata->data = isc_buffer_base(buf);
4354 rdata->length = len;
4355 dns_message_takebuffer(message, &buf);
4356 if (seenpad)
4357 message->padding_off = len;
4358 } else {
4359 rdata->data = NULL;
4360 rdata->length = 0;
4361 }
4362
4363 rdata->rdclass = rdatalist->rdclass;
4364 rdata->type = rdatalist->type;
4365 rdata->flags = 0;
4366
4367 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rdatalist->rdata, rdata, link);
4368 result = dns_rdatalist_tordataset(rdatalist, rdataset);
4369 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
4370
4371 *rdatasetp = rdataset;
4372 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
4373
4374 cleanup:
4375 if (rdata != NULL)
4376 dns_message_puttemprdata(message, &rdata);
4377 if (rdataset != NULL)
4378 dns_message_puttemprdataset(message, &rdataset);
4379 if (rdatalist != NULL)
4380 dns_message_puttemprdatalist(message, &rdatalist);
4381 return (result);
4382}
